Package curam.util.type

Contains the fundamental object type classes that are used by the Curam.

Interface Summary
DateRanged Indicates that the object contains a date range, typically signifying the "lifetime" of the object by virtue of a start and/or end date.
DateTimeRanged Indicates that the object contains a date/time range, typically signifying the "lifetime" of the object by virtue of a start and/or end date/time.
DeepCloneable DeepCloneable is an interface which must be implemented by all Curam value objects to indicate that are responsible for cloning themselves.
HistoricalEvent Signifies that the entity stores a history of events (typically state changes).

Package curam.util.type Description

Contains the fundamental object type classes that are used by the Curam. The main classes include Date, which is the Curam date Object, DateTime, the Curam date and time Object, and Frequency Pattern, which is a flexible way of defining frequencies within Curam.

For more information consult the Curam Developer's guide.

Since:
Curam SDEJ3.0.0
